## Architecture Guidance
{% if arch_type == "microservice" %}
- Include at least 3 distributed system edge cases (network partition, service down, timeout)
- Cover message ordering and duplicate delivery scenarios
- Address circuit breaker and bulkhead failure modes
{% elif arch_type == "modular-monolith" %}
- Cover module boundary violation scenarios
- Address shared database contention patterns
{% else %}
- Cover database transaction edge cases
- Address concurrent user operation conflicts
{% endif %}

{% if dependencies %}
## Dependency-Specific Edge Cases
{% for d in dependencies %}
- What happens when {{ d.target }} is unavailable? ({{ d.pattern }})
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

## Anti-Patterns

Do NOT:
- List only happy-path variations as "edge cases"
- Skip the mitigation strategy
- Use vague scenarios like "something goes wrong"
- Ignore the architecture type's specific failure modes
- Generate fewer than 10 edge cases
